# Web design showcase pattern

Every new design must ship **both** a live interactive demo and a landing-page / catalog preview. Do not ship OG/static thumbnail-only cards.

Reference implementation: **Art** (`id: art`).

## 1. Catalog entry

Add to `designs` in [`apps/web/lib/data.ts`](apps/web/lib/data.ts):

- `id` — kebab-case slug (e.g. `art`)
- `demoPath` — always `/designs/<id>` (ProductFrame + docs)
- `viewPath` — always `/view/<id>` (full-site new-tab preview, no Tawny chrome)
- `title`, `description`, `tags`, `price`, `category`, optional `featured`
- optional `hasThemeSwitch: true` when the design has its own in-demo theme toggle (independent of Tawny)

## 2. Live demo at `/designs/<id>`

Mirror Art’s host pattern:

| Piece | Path |
|-------|------|
| Showcase shell | `apps/web/app/designs/<id>/layout.tsx` |
| App routes | `apps/web/app/designs/<id>/…` (pages, nested layouts) |
| Design UI | `apps/web/components/<id>/…` |
| Design tokens / CSS | e.g. `apps/web/app/designs/<id>/<id>.css` (import from globals if needed) |
| Root shell | Shared `*RootShell` used by showcase + `/view` |

Requirements:

- Wrap the design in [`ProductFrame`](apps/web/components/product-frame.tsx) (window chrome + title like `designs/<id>`)
- Real navigation and interaction inside the frame
- Keep the design self-contained (own fonts/tokens under a root class, e.g. `art-root`)
- Include an **Open in new tab** link to `viewPath` (`target="_blank"`)
- Do **not** iframe the live app on the landing page

## 3. Full-site preview at `/view/<id>`

Mirror the design routes under `apps/web/app/view/<id>/` (thin re-exports of design pages preferred). Requirements:

- No Tawny Navbar/Footer ([`SiteChrome`](apps/web/components/site-chrome.tsx) skips `/view/*`)
- No ProductFrame — edge-to-edge design via the shared root shell
- Navigation helpers must resolve the mount from the pathname (`/designs/<id>` vs `/view/<id>`)
- Discreet “Back to Tawny” link to `demoPath` in production only (hidden in development so screenshot captures stay chrome-free)
- If the design has its own theme (`hasThemeSwitch: true` in `lib/data.ts`), expose an in-demo toggle and isolate via root `data-theme` (not `html.dark`). ProductFrame chrome always follows Tawny’s global theme; demo content may diverge.

## 4. Inert preview mock

Every design needs an inert mock used on **both** the landing showcase and the `/designs` catalog:

1. **Inert mock** — `apps/web/components/landing/<id>-preview-mock.tsx`
   - Visually match the live home (header + main composition)
   - Hardcoded sample copy; no design routing, i18n providers, or data fetches
   - Autoplay / CSS motion OK; **clicks must do nothing** (`inert` / no real links)
   - `role="img"` + accessible name (e.g. “Art design preview”)
2. **Wire into `DesignPreview`** — extend [`apps/web/components/landing/design-preview.tsx`](apps/web/components/landing/design-preview.tsx) so fonts + mock render for the new `id`
3. **Landing showcase** — [`DesignsShowcase`](apps/web/components/landing/designs-showcase.tsx):
   - Independent **Web Designs** section header (not an eyebrow on the first design row)
   - Up to **3** `featured` designs; more designs live on `/designs` (“View all designs”)
   - Rows alternate by index on `lg+`: even = describe | demo, odd = demo | describe; mobile always stacks describe then demo
   - Copy from `lib/data.ts`; preview is `DesignPreview` inside `ProductFrame`
4. **Catalog** — [`/designs`](apps/web/app/designs/page.tsx) cards use `DesignPreview` (clipped), not static images

Only row CTAs (landing “Open live demo”) and the catalog card’s outer link navigate (`demoPath`).

### Optional thumbnail image layer

The inert mock is still required as the fallback for every design and component card. Once a real screenshot is generated, it renders **on top of** the mock — it never replaces the requirement to ship a live demo + mock:

- Generate via the dev-only **Generate screenshot** button next to “Copy page” on `apps/web/app/designs/<id>/layout.tsx` (and on `apps/web/app/components/[id]/page.tsx` for component cards). It posts to `apps/web/app/api/dev/screenshot/route.ts`, which is disabled in production.
- The route captures the live `/view/<id>` (or a component’s `ProductFrame` via selector) with Playwright, compresses it under 500KB with `sharp`, and writes it to `apps/web/public/thumbnails/{designs,components}/<id>.webp`.
- Set `Design.thumbnail` (and `ComponentDemo.thumbnail`) to that path once generated. [`DesignShowcaseRow`](apps/web/components/landing/design-showcase-row.tsx) and [`ComponentDemoCard`](apps/web/components/landing/showcases/component-demo-card.tsx) render the `<img>` (with `object-cover`, so it adapts to the frame at any size) when `thumbnail` is set, and fall back to the mock/live render otherwise.
- If a design’s `viewPath` needs a locale segment to load directly (e.g. Art), set `Design.screenshotPath` to the concrete route to capture.

## 5. Do / don’t

```text
✅ Live app at /designs/<id> inside ProductFrame + Open in new tab → /view/<id>
✅ Full-site /view/<id> without Tawny chrome
✅ Landing: Web Designs section header + copy + inert mock preview (max 3 featured)
✅ Catalog /designs cards use the same inert DesignPreview mocks
✅ Optional generated `thumbnail` screenshot layered on top of the mock (dev-only tool, <500KB, object-cover)

❌ Landing or catalog OG/static cards as the only “showcase” (a live demo + mock must still exist)
❌ Embedding the live route via iframe on the home page
❌ Importing live HomeBento / SiteHeader (or equivalents) into the landing mock
❌ Clickable navigation inside the landing / catalog preview
❌ Putting “Web Designs” as an eyebrow on an individual design row
```

## Checklist for a new design

- [ ] `apps/web/lib/data.ts` entry with `demoPath: '/designs/<id>'` and `viewPath: '/view/<id>'`
- [ ] `apps/web/app/designs/<id>/` live demo + `ProductFrame` + Open in new tab
- [ ] `apps/web/app/view/<id>/` full-site preview (re-exports OK)
- [ ] Navigation mount-aware (`/designs` vs `/view`)
- [ ] If themed: in-demo toggle + root `data-theme` isolation (`hasThemeSwitch: true`); ProductFrame follows Tawny
- [ ] `apps/web/components/landing/<id>-preview-mock.tsx` (inert)
- [ ] Wire into `DesignPreview` (+ `featured: true` only if it should appear in the landing top 3)
- [ ] `/designs` catalog card shows `DesignPreview` + links to `demoPath`
